docs.lead_paragraph: A senior lawmaker from Russia’s ruling party resigned on Wednesday after bloggers revealed that he owned more than $1.3 million in Florida real estate that had not been disclosed.
docs.abstract: Vladimir A Pekhtin, senior lawmaker from Russia’s governing party, resigns from legislature after bloggers reveal that he owned more than $1.3 million worth of luxury real estate in Florida that had not been disclosed; departure sets precedent in Russian government, where high-level corruption and lavish spending overseas has developed into serious political liability.

headline.seo: Russian Lawmaker Quits After Property Disclosure
headline.main: Russian Lawmaker Quits After Real Estate Disclosure
headline.print_headline: Russian Lawmaker Quits After Real Estate Disclosure
